<!-- Body -->

<h4>We encourage companies both to reach out to MIT SWE members through career opportunities 
as well as to directly interact with members through talks and presentations. The following 
are a few of the many ways to connect with MIT SWE.</h4>

<br>

<p><h3>A Day in the Life of...</h3></p>

<p>
<h4><img src="/images/expand.gif">&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/members/companyprofile.php">Read about some of 
the featured companies</a></h4>
</p>
Want to share information about your company with all of members of MIT SWE through its website? Know a female
employee who would serve as a great role model for young women? Email us for more information
on how you can provide SWE members with an insider's look on the great things that happen in your company! 
For more information on how to get involved, contact the webmaster <a href="mailto:kqli@mit.edu">Kimberly Li</a>.

<br><br>
<p><h3>Annual MIT Fall Career Fair and Banquet</h3></p>

<p>
<h4><img src="/images/expand.gif">&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://career-fair.mit.edu/">Find out how to register for 
the 2011 Fall Career Fair</a></h4>
</p>
The MIT Fall Career Fair is co-organized by MIT SWE, and you are invited to the one of the most popular events 
on campus each year! Over 3500 MIT students and alumni attend the career fair to connect with over 
100 companies --- be a part of it! 

<br><br>
<p><h3>Career Events</h3></p>

<p>
<h4><img src="/images/expand.gif">&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="/employers/holdanevent.php">Find out how to collaborate with
SWE and hold a career event</a></h4>
</p>
Many companies come to us to work together on creating an event that features their company and industry. Event topics 
in the past spanned a broad range, and we look forward to working with you in continuing to bring these informative 
opportunities to campus.

<br><br>
<p><h3>Job Postings</h3></p>

<p>
<h4><img src="/images/expand.gif">&nbsp;&nbsp;<a href="http://jobresource.com/groups/ccenter.asp?fct=1&id=986830721">
Take a look at the current job postings exclusively available to MIT SWE members</a></h4>
</p>
If you want to have your company's job posting advertised to the MIT SWE community, please send an email 
to <a href="mailto:swe-cr@mit.edu">swe-cr@mit.edu</a> with a blurb about the position and directions on how 
to make a submission for a posting. We will include your posting in our bi-monthly Corporate Relations Digests 
that detail job opportunities and upcoming events to MIT SWE.

